# Fresh DB Migration Workflow

- This project always recreates the database from scratch during development and ingestion setup.
- Keep Alembic migrations squashed into the current initial state instead of creating follow-up migrations for schema tweaks.
- When schema changes are needed, update `backend/alembic/versions/0001_initial.py` to match the current models and delete superseded follow-up migrations.
- Do not add migration-history bookkeeping tables such as ingestion run history unless the user explicitly asks for persistent run tracking.
- Keep the migration set minimal and aligned with the actual always-fresh database workflow.
